snippet.textDisplay: This video cleared some stuff up for me, thanks! I was honestly disappointed with TRoS, especially after seeing everything TLJ brought to the saga being either destroyed or straight up ignored. instead of building something cohesive and logical, JJ Abrams pandered to those who didn't like TLJ and added a good ol' serving of fan service on top, all that to make a movie completely devoid of heart and truly unoriginal. I liked certain moments of the film (the scenes in/on the ruins of the death star for example were really good and stunning) but I'm so mad at so much of what it does. Bringing back Palpatine and making Rey his grand-daughter (how????), bringing back Lando and barely using him... I'm happy for the people who liked this, like good for you, but this was a disappointing end to such an iconic saga to me.

snippet.textDisplay: My favorite part was the Death Star duel between Rey and Ben, reflecting Obi Wan vs Anakin, and Darth Vader vs Luke, each generation having their own elemental lightsaber battle, with Obi Wan vs Anakin using fire to represent Anakin's coming to the Dark Side, Rey vs Ben using water to represent Ben's coming from the Dark Side, and Luke vs Vader using air to represent Vader's emptiness in his heart. Also, Rey's story arc reflected that of Luke's, that your blood lineage doesn't determine your destiny, while Ben's reflected that of Anakin's, using all his power to save the one he loved. Overall, I believe these were the things that made this a great ending to the Skywalker Saga, paying everything off that was started in previous films.
snippet.textOriginal: My favorite part was the Death Star duel between Rey and Ben, reflecting Obi Wan vs Anakin, and Darth Vader vs Luke, each generation having their own elemental lightsaber battle, with Obi Wan vs Anakin using fire to represent Anakin's coming to the Dark Side, Rey vs Ben using water to represent Ben's coming from the Dark Side, and Luke vs Vader using air to represent Vader's emptiness in his heart. Also, Rey's story arc reflected that of Luke's, that your blood lineage doesn't determine your destiny, while Ben's reflected that of Anakin's, using all his power to save the one he loved. Overall, I believe these were the things that made this a great ending to the Skywalker Saga, paying everything off that was started in previous films.

snippet.textDisplay: I don't know if this counts as an "easter egg" per se, but I appreciated Kylo's room on his ship when Rey was in it. The room was divided by light and dark items, like Ben battling internally with Kylo. The Light outweighed the dark, with just the old Vader helmet being propped up on a black pedestal and 3 objects on the white pedestal (those being the dagger that will actually be a good item in the movie, and Chewies belt and bowcaster). Also just how light and bright his quarters were astounded me. It definitely screamed that he was heavily leaning back to the light side no matter how much he tried to keep up the act of being on the dark side outwardly.
snippet.textOriginal: I don't know if this counts as an "easter egg" per se, but I appreciated Kylo's room on his ship when Rey was in it. The room was divided by light and dark items, like Ben battling internally with Kylo. The Light outweighed the dark, with just the old Vader helmet being propped up on a black pedestal and 3 objects on the white pedestal (those being the dagger that will actually be a good item in the movie, and Chewies belt and bowcaster). Also just how light and bright his quarters were astounded me. It definitely screamed that he was heavily leaning back to the light side no matter how much he tried to keep up the act of being on the dark side outwardly.
